SIMPLE: tew
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tew
<hw>Tew</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Tewed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tewing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>tewen</ets>,
<ets>tawen</ets>. ⟦root⟧64. See <er>Taw</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To prepare by beating or working, as leather or hemp;
to taw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to beat; to scourge; also, to pull about; to
maul; to tease; to vex.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tew</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tew
<hw>Tew</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To work hard; to strive; to
fuse.</def> <mark>[Local]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tew</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tew
<hw>Tew</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Taw</er> to tow,
<er>Tow</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To tow along, as a
vessel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tew</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Tew
<hw>Tew</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A rope or chain for towing a boat;
also, a cord; a string.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tewan</ent>⟦br⟧
